mp3Text: The souls within Yurnero have been awoken.
The rebirth of the Isle of Masks begins with us.
The Isle of Masks will rise again.
Once Yurnero was the last of his kind, but no longer.
The strength of fallen brothers and sisters flows through this body.
We have fought many battles. None as certain as this.
The conclusion is foregone, but honor demands we fight.
Yah, yah yah yah yah, yah, yah.

text: Using  Town Portal Scroll or  Boots of Travel, enemy hero visible within 1200 range

mp3Text: There will be another time to fight…

text: During cast time, no visible enemies within jump radius around target
Although these lines are hooked up, they do not play ingame
Upon ending, 40% of total damage not dealt to heroes

mp3Text: We knew this time would come.
To die at our hand is an honor.
There's a fine line between bravery and stupidity.
Look no more upon our face.
Sven… this isn't some pretend duel where we let you win…
Consider the swift death a courtesy for the kindness you've shown Yurnero.
Your name equals your accomplishments: Tiny.
We had hoped your name was misleading.
Must have been a lesser dragon.
Was there another, better dragon form you could have used?
You could only get back up once?
You're a waste of eternity, Ostarion.
Next time, look before you leap, Huskar.
Was this another attempt at getting sacrificed, Huskar?
Never turn your back in battle.
Any drunken buffoon can pick a fight, Bristleback. It takes a warrior to finish one.
Small town hero, big time flop.
We expected more from you, Tresdin.
Battle's an art, Tresdin, not a show.
This is why Sorla Khan took your place.
This must be what the Rumusque Clerics felt when they purged the Fields of Endless Carnage…
To bury you would defile nature itself.
Your treasures left undefended. For what?
At least your death was honorable, if not your cause.
This was a mercy, sad creature.
Shadows always recede when faced with the light.
You were never going to beat me, Sparkie.
Runner-up in a race of two, Io.
The end of a bloodline, by our hand.
We take no pleasure in your death, Lycan.
A boy's crusade becomes a man's folly.
You should've stuck to fighting scrawny wizards.
Kill the right one and all will fall.
Our blade will always find the truth of things.
A coward's toy will never beat a warrior's blade.
A belt knife would serve you better than that…thing.
Wickedness always comes back around, moon rider.
Now we know what you were hiding from.
There was no bounty on you, Gondar. This was sport.
You've earned your rest, ancient one.
The dreams of your people die with you…
You die as you lived, Troll… Alone.
Your rage is nothing in the face of the Juggernaut.
If only you'd stayed in that temple training acolytes.
You talk big, Wu Kong, but it's just a fairy tale.
Crawl back to your monkey followers, King.
An assassin has no place on this battlefield.
You should have stayed in the shadows, Mortred.
You're not that handy with a blade after all.
This was a long time coming, Slark.
There was no quarrel with you until you brought one, Medusa.
What will become of your sisters now, Medusa?
This is where madness leads, Maiden.
Try to temper your courage with wisdom, Maiden.
You were expecting a different outcome?
Your volatility is predictable, Lina. The limits of discipline? Unknowable.
How many died for your experiments, Tinker? Now you join them.
Yours is a knowledge best lost to the world.
This is what happens when you don't work together.
Smart for an ogre is still just smart for an ogre.
You can only mimic our techniques, Magus.
If you want our respect, Magus, craft something of your own.
No book will stop this blade.
You sought power of the worst kind, Warlock.
With such a mind, you've come to this?
Who will write your epitaph, Auroth?
Should have kept your head in the fight, Wyvern.
What did you think would happen, Techies? It's a battlefield, not a sandbox.
This is all too familiar, Tidehunter!
Your attempts at vengeance are adorable…
When will you learn Siren, you'll never beat us…
You should pick better friends, Puck.
What can a plan do to stop the Juggernaut?
Last of our kind but first in this.
By our word, this ends with honor, Xin. But it does end.
Techies, we'll find you out there. We'll see who's laughing.
Puck. If you couldn't beat us when we were asleep, what chance do you have when we're awake?
Sven, thank you for using the Adjudicator's Blade to awaken us…
We are in your debt Sven, we won't forget this.
You… are a very large piece of rock with a woefully inaccurate name.
Let's show'em what a couple of Dragons can do…
It's nice to know we're not the only half- possessed warrior on the battlefield…
None of your tricks, Wraith King. Let it be a fair fight.
What nature fails to mend, only magic might revive.
Huskar? So much for battle planning.
Signal before you go, Huskar. We'll be ready.
Turning your back on an adversary defies all logic.
Tusk claims he's the better warrior… prove him wrong.
Bristleback claims he's the better warrior… prove him wrong.
Aim higher than barfights, walrusman. You could be something.
You need not fight alone, Tresdin.
People once feared the Bronze Legion… we will make them fear again…
Your technique is lacking, Axe, but we can't argue with the results.
Axe, when this battle is over we must discuss what to do about Sorla Khan.
Stand downwind of your prey, butcher.
After our victory, we wish to hear more about your homeland Pudge…
We are honored to fight at your side, faithful Slithereen.
Duty is a lost art, Slardar.
To fight without purpose is truly madness.
If you were born on the Isle of Masks you would have been fed as mulch to Crex vo Gali…
You rely too much on natural ability, Night Stalker. A warrior knows discipline will take the day.
You work so hard, yet we take all the glory. It's a shame, little friend.
What are you trying to say, Io?
We both have lost something we yearn to restore…
Take heart Lycan, the sounds of battle quiet the cries of those we have lost.
Keep your discipline on this side of zealotry, Anti-Mage.
We heard about your partnership with the Tyler Estate… how's that working out?
It's been too long old friend.
Azwraith, you haven't heard any rumors of Kanna's return have you?
We give your kinfolk credit, Sniper. A small and fragile people, yet you prosper.
Your weapon may be without honor, Sniper, but so is the warrior who would attack one as small as you.
Lanaya… let's just get through this battle without killing each other.
Yurnero is the past Lanaya, you need to move on.
Good deeds cannot erase the past, Luna, but a measure of solace has value all the same.
Where you were lost, now you have found a new home, moon rider.
If an ally's help goes unseen, has he helped at all?
Lead us to the prey, Gondar.
To have lost everything yet remain so true to purpose…
At least you have one companion, Sylla.
The greatest journeys begin in exile, Troll.
Fight with honor and you will always be welcome at our side, Troll.
We should train together more, Xin… It always had… interesting results.
Sun Wu Kong, let us be the first to welcome you to the fight.
You're full of mischief, Monkey King. We hate mischief.
Obedience and honor are not always the same, Assassin.
Perhaps there's some art to your ways after all, Mortred.
We're temporary allies Slark, don't mistake this for friendship.
What use is a beautiful face with no loved ones to gaze upon it?
The power to free your people was worth any price, Medusa.
It's time to set aside childish feuds, Rylai. Family is finite.
Care for yourself as well as others, Maiden, or you'll help no one.
Stop antagonizing your sister, Lina. She might warm up to you.
Your crimes must weigh heavily on your shoulders, Tinker.
Redemption is found by those who seek it, Tinker.
What happens when you both want to do legs, Ogre?
Are you sure you don't want me to remove the extra head?
Stay focused, Magi. If you're lucky, you won't kill yourself.
Not to be pedantic, but it seems more like 'borrowing' spells, Rubick.
What was it like living in Aghanim's shadow?
You read all that in a book, Warlock?
How do you know you're saying the words right, Warlock?
Your mind parts reality like a blade, Invoker.
With a discipline such as yours, Invoker, victory is all but assured.
Our blade writes poetry as well, Auroth.
This plan of yours better work, Techies.
What you do can't be called fighting, Techies.
It's good to fight by your side again, Enchantress.
Together with Enigma, Shadow Shaman, and Rubick, we made history.
Your black hole has changed tide of battle before… it will happen again.
Enigma! What do you say we make history one more time?
Looking forward to beating the odds once more Shadow Shaman?
Yurnero claims that once we made history together…let's do it once more.
They die by our hand, not yours…
This is worth an empty coin purse.
Ah, scepter, relic of a fallen race.
A vessel that holds great power.
This battle is far from over…
We will learn from this defeat…
This failure will not define us…
We were the last of our kind…
One battle is hardly the war.
Back from the brink of extinction.
Best put this aside for now.
Now our stride will match the swiftness of our blade.
Time to hide in plain sight.

Third and more attempts within 10 seconds

mp3Text: With the mask sundered, our souls can finally be free.
We have been freed by The Adjudicator's Blade.
The Isle of Masks is gone, but it won't be forever…
In a past life, we were branded as traitors… And denied a noble death.
Together we will find a way to bring back our people.
Lanaya will not recognize us… It is for the best.
Sven has played his part well.
In battle our honor will be restored.
Once the Ancient is destroyed, our real work can begin.
It is time to find worthy foes…
There is no honor in defeat.
Who can stand against The Juggernaut.
